title: Is Mick Carter murdered? Danny Dyer 'tipped to DIE in EastEnders' goes viral
text:
bbc KILLER? Will Lee murder his dad Mick? 
Mick Carter, played by the legend that is Danny Dyer, is the landlord of the Queen Vic pub. 
But his days screaming "Get out my pub!" may be numbered, if you believe reports that have got everyone chatting online. 
There has been a suggestion that Mick will be murdered by his own son Lee Carter. 
And that Lee will go to Thailand to buy himself a Thai bride. 
Danny-Boy Hatchard, who plays tragic Lee, had noticed something odd about his Wikipedia page and decided to share it on Twitter. 
wiki BOMBSHELL: Is this how Lee will leave EastEnders? Danny Dyer’s Words Of Wisdom Thursday, 8th December 2016 Danny Dyer imparts a whole load of wisdom on the world, as these memorable quotes prove. 1 / 19 “He will leave the soap in 2017 after killing his father Mick Carter” Danny-Boy Hatchard's Wikipedia page 
The career section of the Wikipedia revealed something about Lee's exit, which is due in the coming months as Danny-Boy leaves EastEnders. 
The Wiki page reads: "He was axed in August 2016, and will leave the soap in 2017 after killing his father Mick Carter." 
Mick's tragic (and rather surprising end) will happen in "a dramatic fight outside the Archers over [Lee's] debt," it adds. 
While this would certainly make for a dramatic ending, we're having a hard time believing it. 
twitter WTF? Viewers believed the post
